nd in Haiti. Compare   Montfort   1, see also 2 below.","Altered form of Dutch <b>Montfoort</b>, a variant of   Montfort   2 and also a cognate of the French name in 1 above and an altered form of its variant   Montfort   1 (or perhaps vice versa)."]},{"name":"Monforte","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Italian Angelo, Salvatore, Carmela, Carmine, Rocco, Rosaria, Sal.  Spanish Carlos, Francisco, Luis, Medardo.","Italian and Spanish: habitational name from any of numerous places called Monforte, from Latin <i>mons</i> ‘mountain’ (genitive <i>montis</i>) + <i>fortis</i> ‘strong’, probably a reference to the strategic position of these locations.","English (of Norman origin): variant of   Montfort  . This form of the surname is rare in Britain."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Guiburge De Montfort was born in 1182, in Montfort-l'Amaury, Yvelines, Île-de-France, France, her father, Simon de Montfort l'Amaury IV, was 7 and her mother, Amice De Beaumont Of Leicester, was 29. She married Guy De LÉvis in 1210, in Mirepoix, Ariège, Occitanie, France. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter. She died in 1234, in France, at the age of 52."},"et":{"1182–1234":"1182–1234","1180–1230":"1180–1230","1210–1247":"1210–1247","1230–1284":"1230–1284","1175–1218":"1175–1218","1154–1215":"1154–1215","25 June 1218":"25. juuni 1218","December 1230":"detsember 1230","1154":"1154","1230":"1230","1175":"1175","1284":"1284","15 janvier 1210":"15. jaanuar 1210","1182":"1182","1180":"1180","1215":"1215","1247":"1247","1234":"1234","3 September 1215":"3. september 1215","1210":"1210","1218":"1218","Rochefort, Charente-Maritime, France.":"Rochefort, Charente-Maritime, Nouvelle-Aquitaine, Prantsusmaa","Mirepoix, Ariege, France":"Mirepoix, Ariège, Prantsusmaa","Toulouse, Haute-Garonne, France":"Toulouse, Haute-Garonne, Prantsusmaa","Montfort-l'Amaury, Yvelines, Île-de-France, France":"Montfort-l'Amaury, Yvelines, Île-de-France, Prantsusmaa","Mirepoix, Ariège, Occitanie, France":"Mi